# VoiceVault — Native Services & AI/ML Pipeline Architecture

## Service Architecture Overview

**Core Principle:** All heavy compute, native modules, and AI/ML inference run in the **main process**. The renderer is a thin UI layer.

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      Main Process Services                      │
│                   (Node.js + Native Addons)                     │
├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  AudioCaptureService        → native-audio-node (CoreAudio)     │
│  WhisperService             → whisper-cpp-node (CoreML)         │
│  DiarizationService         → pyannote-cpp-node                 │
│  LLMService                 → node-llama-cpp (GGUF models)      │
│  DatabaseService            → better-sqlite3                    │
│  VectorService              → Local embeddings + HNSW search    │
│  ExportService              → Obsidian markdown, PDF            │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              │ IPC
                              ▼
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      Renderer Process                           │
│                   (React + UI, zero compute)                    │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Service Lifecycle
Each service follows a consistent lifecycle:
1. **Constructor** — Initialize state, no side effects
2. **`initialize()`** — Load models, open connections (async)
3. **`start()`** — Begin operations (e.g., start capture, start inference)
4. **`stop()`** — Pause operations, preserve state
5. **`cleanup()`** — Release resources, close connections, unload models

