## Memory Management for Large Models

### Best Practices
1. **Lazy-load models** — Don't load at app startup, load on first use
2. **Unload when idle** — Free memory after 5 minutes of inactivity
3. **Monitor memory** — Use `process.memoryUsage()` to track heap size
4. **Limit concurrent jobs** — Only one transcription/summarization at a time
5. **Stream outputs** — Don't accumulate full results in memory

### Example: Lazy Loading
```typescript
class WhisperService {
  private model: WhisperCpp.Model | null = null
  private idleTimer: NodeJS.Timeout | null = null
  
  async transcribe(audioPath: string) {
    // ✅ Load model on demand
    if (!this.model) {
      await this.loadModel()
    }
    
    // Reset idle timer
    this.resetIdleTimer()
    
    // ... transcribe
  }
  
  private resetIdleTimer(): void {
    if (this.idleTimer) clearTimeout(this.idleTimer)
    
    this.idleTimer = setTimeout(() => {
      console.log('[WhisperService] Unloading model due to inactivity')
      this.unloadModel()
    }, 5 * 60 * 1000)  // 5 minutes
  }
  
  private unloadModel(): void {
    if (this.model) {
      this.model = null
      // Force garbage collection (if --expose-gc flag set)
      if (global.gc) global.gc()
    }
  }
}
```

